(2, 1, '2011-02-15 01:32:35', '2011-02-15 01:32:35', 'A friend asked me what I do all day as a web designer. I told him I stare at a computer screen and type in code that looks like pictures to everyone else. He sarcastically declared that I practiced witchcraft. I later learned thatÂ Arthur C. Clarke, the author of "2001: A Space Oddessy" shared my friend''sÂ assessment. In the last of Clarke''s three laws he stated,\r\n\r\n[quote type="center]Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from magic. [/quote]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThat is what I hope to do wiht this web design firm. Do my job well enough that it comes across like a bit of magic. I want to accomplish that in my designs, the way the you interact with your site when you make changes, and my relationship with you as we build a web presence for your business.', 'Third Law Web Design', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'about', '', '', '2014-06-13 07:38:23', '2014-06-13 07:38:23', '', 0, 'http://third-law.com/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
