(224, 1, '2014-03-26 23:31:21', '2014-03-26 23:31:21', '<strong><a href="http://third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/drupal-vs-wordpress.gif"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-309" src="http://localhost/third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/drupal-vs-wordpress-300x184.png" alt="drupal-vs-wordpress" width="300" height="184" /></a>Website Design with WordPress is far less complicated than Drupal.</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is the main reason to choose WordPress instead of Drupal. If you do not have a technical background Drupal is just going to be one headache after another. It is easy enough for just about anyone who is able to navigate the web to maintain a site built on the Wordpress platform. To get the site up and going with a good design that keepsÂ searchÂ engines in mind, you will need Â a quality web designer. But the maintaining of the site and even adding new features can be done by someone with basic webÂ experience.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Software and plugins are easy to update.</strong>\r\n\r\nWordPress updates are dead simple: A couple of quick clicks and all theÂ essentialsÂ can be updated. Â This is not the case with Drupal. Updating the Drupal coreÂ requires technical know-how beyond the comfort level of even many tech-orientatedÂ individuals. It is common when upgrading to a new version of Drupal that most clients call their web developer to accomplish the task.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Website Customization is intuitive.</strong>\r\n\r\nWordPress was designed to use things called "widgets". Â Widgets provide a quick way to customize your site by adding specialized items (an e-newsletter signup, a Twitter feed and so on) to your website. There is alot of stuff going on behind the scenes, but all you see is a super easy to use drag and drop interface. You move what you want where you want. Â Drupal makes it harder for non-technical folks to customize a website.\r\n\r\n<em>Website design with Wordpress is the best choice for theÂ i