(324, 1, '2014-04-13 05:22:59', '2014-04-13 05:22:59', 'The Prescott Area Art Trust is responsible for all the bronze statues you see in the courthouse square in downtown Prescott. They needed a website to get the word out about what they do, raise some awareness (and some money too), so they can put up more monuments.\r\n\r\nThey were looking for a site that would with a dusty, western feeling that would evoke images of the Old West without having to resort to images of lassos and spurs. They also wanted it to have a gallery feeling without being black which is the typical color choice for gallery design. So, dusty yet elegant.\r\n\r\nThe site displays all their statues, but has special attention on the Rough Rider miniature statues that are being sold as a fundraiser for more bronze-work.\r\n\r\nStatus: Design is complete. The client is currently preparing content.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/new_homepage1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-179" title="new_homepage" src="http://third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/new_homepage1-917x1024.jpg" alt="" width="387" height="432" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/post_layout3.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-215" title="Prescott Area Art Trust" src="http://third-law.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/post_layout3-1024x965.jpg" alt="" width="378" height="356" /></a>', 'Prescott Area Art Trust', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'open', '', 'prescott-area-art-trust-2', '', '', '2014-06-13 06:09:07', '2014-06-13 06:09:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost/third-law.com/?p=324', 0, 'post', '', 0),
